---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Terms and Conditions">
  <main class="flex justify-center w-full">
    <div class="max-w-prose prose py-20 flex flex-col gap-0">
      <h1 class="text-secondary-300 text-2xl font-black text-center pb-8">
        Terms and Conditions
      </h1>
      <h2 id="1-introduction">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Welcome to [Event Name] organized by [Organization Name]. By purchasing a
        ticket and participating in the event, you agree to comply with and
        be bound by the following terms and conditions.
      </p>
      <h2 id="2-organizer-information">2. Organizer Information</h2>
      <p>[Event Name] is organized by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>[Organization Name]</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Sales are facilitated by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>[Ticket Provider]</li>
        <li>[Payment Processor]</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 id="3-ticket-purchase">3. Ticket Purchase</h2>
      <h3 id="3-1-general">3.1 General</h3>
      <p>
        Tickets for the event can be purchased online through our designated ticket provider.
        All ticket sales are final, and no refunds will be issued unless otherwise stated.
      </p>
      <h3 id="3-2-payment">3.2 Payment</h3>
      <p>
        All payments are processed securely through our payment processor. By
        purchasing a ticket, you agree to their respective terms of service and
        privacy policies.
      </p>
      <h3 id="3-3-confirmation">3.3 Confirmation</h3>
      <p>
        Upon successful payment, you will receive a confirmation email with your
        ticket details. Please ensure that your email address is accurate during the
        registration process.
      </p>
      <h2 id="4-cancellations-and-refunds">4. Cancellations and Refunds</h2>
      <h3 id="4-1-organizer-cancellation">4.1 Organizer Cancellation</h3>
      <p>
        In the unlikely event that the event is canceled by the organizers,
        ticket holders will be notified about the refund policy. The organizers are not
        responsible for any additional expenses incurred by ticket holders.
      </p>
      <h3 id="4-2-attendee-cancellation">4.2 Attendee Cancellation</h3>
      <p>
        Refund policies for attendee cancellations will be clearly stated during the ticket
        purchase process.
      </p>
      <h2 id="5-code-of-conduct">5. Code of Conduct</h2>
      <h3 id="5-1-expected-behavior">5.1 Expected Behavior</h3>
      <p>
        All attendees, speakers, sponsors, and volunteers at the event are
        required to agree with the code of conduct. Organizers will
        enforce this code throughout the event. We expect cooperation from all
        participants to help ensure a safe environment for everybody.
      </p>
      <h3 id="5-2-unacceptable-behavior">5.2 Unacceptable Behavior</h3>
      <p>
        Harassment of any kind will not be tolerated. Any attendee violating these 
        rules may be sanctioned or expelled from the event without a refund at the 
        discretion of the organizers.
      </p>
      <h2 id="6-liability">6. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        The organizers do not accept responsibility for any personal injury,
        loss, or damage to property during the event. Attendees are responsible
        for their own belongings.
      </p>
      <h2 id="7-privacy-policy">7. Privacy Policy</h2>
      <h3 id="7-1-data-collection">7.1 Data Collection</h3>
      <p>
        By purchasing a ticket, you consent to the collection and processing of
        your personal data for the purposes of event registration and
        communication.
      </p>
      <h3 id="7-2-data-usage">7.2 Data Usage</h3>
      <p>
        Your personal data will be used to facilitate your attendance at the
        event and to provide you with relevant information. Your
        data will not be shared with third parties without your explicit
        consent, except as required by law.
      </p>
      <h2 id="8-changes-to-terms-and-conditions">
        8. Changes to Terms and Conditions
      </h2>
      <p>
        The organizers reserve the right to update and change these terms and
        conditions at any time. Any changes will be posted on the official
        event website.
      </p>
      <h3 id="9-consent-to-recording">9. Consent to Recording</h3>
      <p>
        By attending the event, you consent to being photographed, filmed,
        and recorded. These materials may be used by the organizers for promotional 
        and marketing purposes. If you do not wish to be photographed or recorded, please
        notify the organizers upon arrival.
      </p>
      <h2 id="10-governing-law">10. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms and conditions are governed by the laws of [Jurisdiction].
        Any disputes arising from or in connection with these terms and conditions 
        will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of [Jurisdiction].
      </p>
      <h2 id="11-contact-information">11. Contact Information</h2>
      <p>
        For any questions regarding these terms and conditions, please contact
        us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        Email: [contact@example.com]<br />
        Phone: [+1 234 567 890]<br/>
        Address: [123 Event Street, City, Country, ZIP]
      </p>
      <p>
        Thank you for your understanding and cooperation. We look forward to
        welcoming you to [Event Name].
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
